article.headline: Buffalo 81, Bowling Green 67
article.story: AMHERST, N.Y. (AP) -- Calvin Cage led Buffalo with 21 points as the Bulls defeated Bowling Green 81-67 Sunday in Mid-American Conference play. Yassin Idbihi and Mario Jordan added 19 points and 10 rebounds each for Buffalo (17-11, 7-9). Bowling Green (9-18, 5-11) lost its fifth straight. The Falcons committed 17 turnovers that led to 23 Buffalo points. Martin Samarco led the Falcons with 23 points. John Floyd scored 15. Buffalo led 37-34 at halftime, then started the second half with a 12-0 run.
